        "title": "fix(template): resolve variable shadowing in export-html template",
        "body": "## What Problem This Solves\nRenamed three local bindings (`data`, `base64`, `leafId`) in `src/auto-reply/reply/export-html/template.js` to avoid shadowing top-level names. This removes name collision risk and improves code clarity/maintainability.\n\n## Evidence\n```text\n=== Template.js Validation ===\n\nTest command: node --check src/auto-reply/reply/export-html/template.js\n✓ JavaScript syntax is valid\n\nFile details:\n66408 bytes\n\nFixes applied (no-shadow):\n- Line 702: function sanitizeImageBase64(base64Data) - parameter renamed from 'data'\n- Line 715: const imgBase64 - local variable renamed from 'base64'  \n- Line 867: const targetLeafId - click handler variable renamed from 'leafId'\n```\n\nNo changes to HTML export behavior - only internal variable names were updated for clarity.\n\n## Context\nNote: This file is currently excluded from oxlint coverage (see .oxlintrc.json line 218), so these changes are **preventive code quality improvements** rather than fixes for enforced lint failures. The renamed variables eliminate potential confusion where inner scope variables shadow outer scope names, improving code readability and maintainability.",
